    <h2>Our Vision</h2>
    <p>We envision a world where technology amplifies Christian charity, creating efficient, compassionate systems that serve the poor, feed the hungry, and bring hope to the hopeless. Through the marriage of ancient faith and modern innovation, we strive to be the hands and feet of Christ in the digital age.</p>
    
    <h2>Theological Foundation</h2>
    <p>Our work is rooted in the pre-schism Christian tradition, drawing from the wisdom of the early Church Fathers and the undivided Church of the first millennium. We believe that:</p>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Faith and Reason Unite</strong>: As St. John Chrysostom taught, faith and reason are not opponents but partners in understanding God's will.</li>
        <li><strong>Technology is a Tool for Good</strong>: When guided by Christian ethics, technology can multiply our capacity to serve others.</li>
        <li><strong>Charity is Worship</strong>: Serving the poor is a form of liturgy, offering our work as a living sacrifice to God.</li>
        <li><strong>Unity in Diversity</strong>: We welcome Christians from all traditions who share our commitment to serving Christ through serving others.</li>
    </ul>
    
